&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Smart Buildings team at DLR Group&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DLR Group’s approach is unique because we start every project with a focus on building performance outcomes and use this as a guide to inform our integrated design process. The Commissioning process is central to our approach, ensuring quality and consistency throughout design and construction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our certified Commissioning Authorities, Energy Management experts and Professional Engineers combine &lt;strong&gt;design&lt;/strong&gt; phase expertise with hands-on &lt;strong&gt;functional testing&lt;/strong&gt; and advanced &lt;strong&gt;operational performance analytics&lt;/strong&gt;. This ensures projects are delivered at peak performance on Day One of operations, and are equipped for long-term efficiency and success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We focus the Commissioning process to be the formal framework for delivering low-carbon, high-performance designs that elevate the human experience and deliver real value for building owners by prioritizing operational efficiency, occupant health and resilience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this position, you will be supporting commissioning activities for multiple high-profile, national and international Commissioning projects across DLR Group’s core sectors including Workplace, Federal, Education, Hospitality, Healthcare, Justice &amp;amp; Civic, Mixed-Use and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dlrgroup.com/work/&quot;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;. You will work with these integrated design teams of Architects, Engineers and specialty designers, providing commissioning expertise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Commissioning Authority, you will frequently travel to job sites to perform construction reviews, functional testing, and building performance diagnostics. Expect to be traveling approximately 30–50% of your time in a typical month. In this role there is potential for rapid growth opportunities as we expand our Smart Buildings team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful candidate will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review design and construction documents for compliance with Owner’s Project Requirements and Basis of Design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop commissioning plans, specifications, pre-functional checklists, and functional performance tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform site inspections and functional testing to verify system installation and operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with contractors, owners, occupants, and operators to identify improvements on building operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, track, and resolve issues impacting system performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide feedback to design teams to ensure optimal design strategies.

