&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Designer, Intermediate – &lt;/strong&gt;DLR Group, Inc. (Boston, MA). Responsible for daily design and technical development of architectural building projects; coordinate all aspects of the project document development and delivery; and, collaborate with all integrated design project team members to produce quality work products while adhering to project schedules, project budgets and work plans. Requires Bachelor’s degree in Architecture or closely related field plus 6 years’ professional experience with architectural design. Requires demonstrated proficiency with: Revit; Bluebeam; Architecture software including AutoCAD and Designer Pages Pro; 3D visualizing software including Enscape, SketchUp, and Lumion Render; technical design aspects of assigned projects, including investigation, evaluation and recommendation of design solutions that best meet the client’s need; and, design techniques, tools and sustainable design principles involved in the production of precision technical plans, drawings, reports, models and related deliverables. $98,530 - $108,350/year. Four days in-office with flexibility to work remote on Fridays. Apply at dlrgroup.com/careers, reference ID 3561.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits –&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Our comprehensive Benefits at DLR Group include medical, dental, vision, disability, wellness programs, flex spending, paid holidays, and paid time off. We also offer a 401(k) plan, employee stock ownership, and bonus opportunities. Compensation considerations are based on location, experience, and skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We operate within a hybrid work model, supporting flexibility between office time and work from home. This role will work on-site at our Boston, MA office Monday to Thursday, with flexibility to work remotely on Fridays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-DNI&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.dlrgroup.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-cke-saved-href=&quot;http://www.dlrgroup.com/&quot;&gt;DLR Group&lt;/a&gt; is an integrated design firm delivering architecture, engineering, interiors, planning, and building optimization for new builds, renovations, and adaptive reuse projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are 100% employee-owned: every employee is literally invested in our clients’ success. At the core of our firm are interdisciplinary teams engaged in every step of project lifecycles. Our teams champion true collaboration, open information sharing, shared risk and reward, value-based decision making, and proficient use of technology to deliver exceptional design. We are pursuing the goals of the 2030 Challenge, the ME2040, and the SE2050, and are an initial signatory of the China Accord and the AIA 2030 Commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through our values – commitment, creativity, environmental stewardship, fun, integrity, ownership, sharing, teamwork – we elevate the human experience through design, together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;DLR Group follows a four-day in-office work model, with employees having the flexibility to work somewhere other than the office on Fridays.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud to be an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action/M/F/Veteran/Disabled employer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/di

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.dlrgroup.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-cke-saved-href=&quot;http://www.dlrgroup.com/&quot;&gt;DLR Group&lt;/a&gt; is an integrated design firm with a promise to elevate the human experience through design. This fuels the work we do around the world and inspires our mission to improve the lives of our clients, our communities, and our planet. If this sparks your interest, you’re in the right place.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Design Technology&lt;/strong&gt; team has an opening for an &lt;strong&gt;Entry-Level Design Technology Manager&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;in our&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;L&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;os Angeles&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;studio. While Los Angeles is the preferred location for this role, we are also open to considering candidates based in our other California studios; a list of locations can be found &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dlrgroup.com/firm/locations/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a DLR Group &lt;strong&gt;Entry-Level &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design Technology Manager,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;you will support project teams across the firm by implementing BIM best practices and ensuring efficient use of design technology tools. You will serve as a resource to our architects, engineers, and designers throughout all project phases—helping teams navigate Revit workflows, resolve model performance issues, and leverage digital tools that improve quality and productivity. You will also support the coordination of BIM workflows between project teams, clients, consultants, and contractors. Your work enables our teams to operate at their highest level and deliver exceptional design outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct periodic quality assurance reviews of Revit models and provide actionable feedback to project teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support BIM Execution Planning, including project setup through established startup portals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with design teams to resolve Revit model performance issues and ensure adherence to best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with Navisworks setup for clash detection and coordination reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain Revit content and integrate standards updates into active project files&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the management and organization of BIM 360 project sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current with design technology tools, software updates, and add-ons used in production workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver or coordinate training and knowledge-sharing sessions to help teams adopt new tools and workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide feedback to senior Design Technology Managers on opportunities to enhance BIM standards and improve project-wide efficiencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-5 years of Architecture/Engineering/Construction (A/E/C) related Design Technology experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Revit in a production or academic setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to learn new software quickly and apply new digital skills effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills with the ability to explain technical concepts clearly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage and prioritize multiple tasks in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Dynamo, Grasshopper, or another visual programming or scripting language&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educational background in Architecture, Interior Design, Engineering, or a related design discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
